Hi

I was wondering how do I create a repo for an organization?
I have the following code but it keps creating the repo in my private space and not the organization space. The owner always shows as my private account and not the organization

```
GitHub github = null;

       try {
            github = new GitHubBuilder().withOAuthToken(personalAccessToken,"my-org").build();
        } catch (IOException e) {
            System.out.println("An IOException has occured. Exception is: " + e);
        }
        GHRepository ghHRepository = null;
        try {
            ghHRepository = github.createRepository(repositoryName).projects(true).autoInit(true).wiki(true).private_(false).create();
        } catch (IOException e) {
            System.out.println("Repository: An IOException has occured creating the repository. Exception is: " + e);
        }
        System.out.println("New ghHRepository:" + ghHRepository);
        System.out.println("New ghHRepository owner:" + ghHRepository.getOwnerName());
        return ghHRepository;
```

Thanks
Damien

# Description 
Github asked that the name of the org be changed to prevent people from mistaking this project for an official GitHub project. 

I don't expect anyone to go through all the test files to check all the changes, but you can get a sense for them.

@kohsuke  If you would rather take the project back to your personal account, we can use this change as the basis - it will be easy to search and replace "hub4j" to "kohsuke". 

Fixes #801

@kohsuke @oleg-nenashev

**Describe the bug**

When a repository has a license type that is unclear, such as a mixture of licenses, or is identified as `Other`, the `GHLicense`'s fields aren't properly parsed/populated and this causes `NullPointerException`-s.

An example of such a repository is https://github.com/bndtools/bnd/ . In this case, the project is under multiple license and it appears they're all in the same license file.

Code:
```
GitHub gitHub = GitHub.connectAnonymously();
GHRepository repository = gitHub.getRepository(repositoryId);

GHLicense ghLicense = repository.getLicense();

System.out.println(ghLicense.getName());

if (ghLicense.getUrl() != null)
// Without this null check, this will also throw a NullPointerException
// as the one shown below:
{
    System.out.println(ghLicense.getUrl().toString());
}

License license = new License(ghLicense.getName(),
                              ghLicense.getDescription(), // This throws a NullPointerException
                              ghLicense.getUrl().toString);  // This also throws a NullPointerException

```

Exception:
```
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NullPointerException
	at org.kohsuke.github.GitHubRequest$Builder.withUrlPath(GitHubRequest.java:608)
	at org.kohsuke.github.GHLicense.populate(GHLicense.java:202)
	at org.kohsuke.github.GHLicense.getDescription(GHLicense.java:114)
```


**Expected behavior**

This should be error-proofed and not crash.
